<BaseLayout
  title="Resources"
  description="Books, articles, research papers, and talks on effective leadership. The sources behind Leader Smells."
>
  <h1>Resources</h1>

  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
    The research and reading that informed Leader Smells. Everything here is worth
    your time if you want to understand what makes leadership effective — or
    destructive.
  </p>

  <h2>Essential Books</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.calnewport.com/books/deep-work/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Deep Work</strong>
      </a>
      by Cal Newport — The science of focused work and why constant connectivity
      destroys productivity. Essential for understanding The Update Addict and
      Calendar Tetris patterns.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Fearless-Organization-Psychological-Workplace-Innovation/dp/1119477247" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>The Fearless Organization</strong>
      </a>
      by Amy Edmondson — Psychological safety research applied to teams. Key
      reading for The Firefighter Hero and Invisible Goalpost patterns.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Flow-Psychology-Experience-Perennial-Classics/dp/0061339202" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience</strong>
      </a>
      by Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi — Understanding flow states and what conditions
      make them possible (or impossible).
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Drive-Surprising-Truth-About-Motivates/dp/1594484805" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Drive</strong>
      </a>
      by Daniel Pink — Autonomy, mastery, and purpose as the core drivers of
      motivation. Explains why micromanagement backfires.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Radical-Candor-Revised-Kick-Ass-Humanity/dp/1250235375" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Radical Candor</strong>
      </a>
      by Kim Scott — How to care personally while challenging directly.
      An antidote to many leader smells.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://basecamp.com/books/remote" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Remote: Office Not Required</strong>
      </a>
      by Jason Fried & DHH — Async-first work culture and why meetings aren't
      the answer. Essential for The Sync Maximalist pattern.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Managers-Path-Leaders-Navigating-Growth/dp/1491973897" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>The Manager's Path</strong>
      </a>
      by Camille Fournier — A practical guide for tech leaders at every level.
      Solid advice for avoiding most leader smells.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Key Research Papers & Articles</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://paulgraham.com/makersschedule.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Maker's Schedule, Manager's Schedule</strong>
      </a>
      by Paul Graham — The foundational essay on why meetings destroy maker
      productivity.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.2307/2666999" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Psychological Safety and Learning Behavior in Work Teams</strong>
      </a>
      by Amy Edmondson (1999) — The original research on psychological safety
      in teams.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://selfdeterminationtheory.org/SDT/documents/2000_RyanDeci_SDT.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>Self-Determination Theory</strong>
      </a>
      by Deci & Ryan — The foundational research on intrinsic motivation and
      the need for autonomy.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://hbr.org/2013/12/how-google-sold-its-engineers-on-management" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>How Google Sold Its Engineers on Management</strong>
      </a>
      — Harvard Business Review on Google's Project Oxygen and what makes
      managers effective.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.gallup.com/workplace/247391/fixable-problem-costs-businesses-trillion.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>This Fixable Problem Costs U.S. Businesses $1 Trillion</strong>
      </a>
      — Gallup's research on employee turnover and what drives it.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/blog/productivity/the-future-of-work-is-asynchronous" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>The Future of Work is Asynchronous</strong>
      </a>
      — Atlassian on async-first companies and why they outperform.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://fellow.ai/resources/state-of-meetings-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>State of Meetings Report 2024</strong>
      </a>
      — Fellow's comprehensive data on meeting overload.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/blog/loom/cost-of-context-switching" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>The Cost of Context Switching</strong>
      </a>
      — Atlassian's breakdown of the research on interruptions.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Talks & Videos</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/amy_edmondson_how_to_turn_a_group_of_strangers_into_a_team" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>How to Turn a Group of Strangers into a Team</strong>
      </a>
      — Amy Edmondson's TED talk on psychological safety.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/dan_pink_the_puzzle_of_motivation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>The Puzzle of Motivation</strong>
      </a>
      — Dan Pink on why traditional incentives don't work for creative work.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=arj7oStGLkU" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <strong>RSA Animate: Drive</strong>
      </a>
      — Animated summary of Dan Pink's research on motivation.
    </li>
  </ul>

